Lagos State Chapter of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) has commiserated with the families of those who lost their dear ones in the explosion that occurred in Abule Ado, in Amuwo Odofin local government area of Lagos State. The state’s Chairman of the party, Engineer Deji Doherty who stated this while receiving the Action Democratic party ADP governorship candidate in the last general elections Babatunde Gbadamosi and his supporters to the PDP urged the state and federal government to get to the root cause of the explosion. He said the explosion could have been caused due to negligence on the part of some set of individuals and government, saying a thorough investigation was necessary to know what led to the explosion and as well fashioned out a way to prevent such a recurrence. Gbadamosi who was a former member of the PDP joined ADP to actualise his governorship ambition. Receiving him back to the party, Doherty said if cases of similar incident in the past has been properly investigated, it could have forestall a repeat of such incident. Doherty noted that it is not every time one play politics with issues, just as he condemned engaging in rhetoric when drastic step ought to be taken to prevent a reoccurrence of bad incident. He charged the National Emergency Agency NEMA and State Emergency Agencies to be alive to their responsibility and also engage in proactive measure that can prevent similar incident. 